  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I'd like to have a list of available MailServers for each network so I can switch between networks and still be able to communicate with people being offline.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Feature\r\n\r\n*Summary*: Currently, we have a single list of MailServers that are used for every network, however, it's incorrect. A given MailServer can work only with a specific network.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nThe user can switch between networks and still have the offline messaging working properly.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nA list of MailServers is hardcoded and works only with Ropsten. When switching to e.g. Rinkeby or Mainnet, provided MailServers do not work.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n1. Open Status,\r\n2. Start talking in Ropsten and make sure offline messaging works,\r\n3. Switch to another network and make sure offline messaging works as well.\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\nProvide at least one MailServer for each network: Ropsten, Rinkeby, Mainnet.",
